{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SvzguuXbjEmLfsSHyqTVwv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01F81mjQ26vaP2cNozxfQdMu","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Verify story 18-3 test-provable","prompt":"Verify story 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation using local CLI checks (test-provable tier).\n\nStory file: /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation.md\n\nExecute these steps and report results:\n1. Run the project build command (`npm run build` in /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness). Report: PASS or FAIL + first 10 error lines.\n2. Run tests (`npm run test:unit` in /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness). Report: PASS (N passed) or FAIL (N failed: list names).\n3. Run coverage (`npm run test:coverage` in /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness). Report: coverage percentage.\n4. For each AC in the story file (there are 10 ACs), verify it with concrete evidence:\n\n   **AC 1**: Clean merge → test suite runs → MergeResult.success true with testResults. Check that worktree-manager.ts calls validateMerge and returns success with testResults. Grep for validateMerge in worktree-manager.ts and check test output for related test names.\n   \n   **AC 2**: Test failure after clean merge → merge reverted, MergeResult { success: false, reason: 'tests-failed' }. Check worktree-manager.ts handles validation.valid === false with revert + that reason. Check tests cover this case.\n   \n   **AC 3**: Test failure after agent resolution → retry with context up to 3 attempts. Check merge-agent.ts uses validateMerge in retry loop with output appended as context. Check tests.\n   \n   **AC 4**: Test results written as telemetry entry to .codeharness/telemetry.jsonl. Check cross-worktree-validator.ts writes telemetry via writeTelemetryEntry or similar. Check tests mock/verify telemetry writes.\n   \n   **AC 5**: Uses configured test command with 5-minute timeout. Check validateMerge accepts testCommand param and uses 300_000 timeout. Check tests.\n   \n   **AC 6**: New src/lib/cross-worktree-validator.ts exports validateMerge(options: ValidateMergeOptions): Promise<ValidationResult>. Check file exists and exports are correct.\n   \n   **AC 7**: ValidationResult interface has: valid, testResults { passed, failed, coverage? }, output, durationMs. Grep for the interface definition.\n   \n   **AC 8**: ValidateMergeOptions interface has: testCommand, cwd, epicId, storyKey?, writeTelemetry. Grep for the interface definition.\n   \n   **AC 9**: When writeTelemetry=true, telemetry entry has storyKey='merge-{epicId}'. Check the telemetry write function and tests.\n   \n   **AC 10**: All existing worktree-manager and merge-agent tests pass — no regressions. Confirmed by step 2 passing.\n\n5. Report each AC as PASS or FAIL with one-line evidence.\n6. Generate proof document at /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation-proof.md with evidence from each check. Use the format:\n   ```\n   # Verification Proof: 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation\n   \n   Story: Cross-Worktree Test Validation\n   Verified: {timestamp}\n   Tier: test-provable\n   \n   ## AC 1: {description}\n   \n   **Verdict:** PASS/FAIL\n   \n   ```bash\n   {command run}\n   ```\n   ```output\n   {relevant output}\n   ```\n   \n   {repeat for each AC}\n   \n   ## Summary\n   \n   - Total ACs: 10\n   - Passed: N\n   - Failed: N\n   - Escalated: 0\n   ```\n\n7. Run `codeharness verify --story 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation` to validate the proof format.\n8. Report final result: ALL_PASS (N/N ACs) or PARTIAL (M/N ACs, list failures).\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commands. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, missing files, unexpected behavior)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky or suboptimal)\n- Verification gaps (ACs that were hard to verify, weak evidence)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N unique, M total reads (list any file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: describe any repeated reads, duplicate commands, or wasted calls","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":462,"cache_read_input_tokens":50744,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":462},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"463e753d-ff5b-4757-9453-b6d867bfb166","uuid":"6afbf760-0c0a-4151-821d-f6bd93a526ff"}
