{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014mQyqVuwE3urgw1p8asAuT","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"463e753d-ff5b-4757-9453-b6d867bfb166","uuid":"18f6b08a-5149-48fd-b1dc-5a5be65aa6f6","timestamp":"2026-04-03T22:50:25.051Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Redundant operations: Two separate coverage commands that didn't yield isolated file percentage","newString":"- Redundant operations: Two separate coverage commands that didn't yield isolated file percentage\n\n### 19-1-epic-completion-detection — create-story (2026-04-04T02:54)\n\n- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent (per instructions) — orchestrator handled.\n- No config.yaml at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — found at `_bmad/config.yaml` instead.\n- No project-context.md found — not a blocker, sufficient context from epics/architecture.\n- EpicState.status is `string` not a union type — story handles via local `EpicLifecycleStatus` type.\n- All 10 ACs tagged test-provable — pure functions, no I/O.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 10, Glob: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff HEAD~3 --name-only (~35 lines), sprint-state.json (~40 lines), git log (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04\n\n### 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration — verification (2026-04-04T01:10)\n\n- Proof document used `### AC N:` headers instead of `## AC N:` — validator couldn't parse. Fixed by rewriting proof.\n- No `bash`+`output` code block pairs in original proof — added evidence blocks.\n- Subagent misreported test compilation failure (Babel/Jest) when project uses vitest.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 5\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 1 unique, 1 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — create-story (2026-04-04T01:13)\n\n- No project-context.md found — context gathered from architecture and epics files.\n- Workaround: inline AsyncMutex class pattern rather than npm dependency.\n- Risk: AC #7 (NFR4 timing) depends on repo size/disk speed, tagged runtime-provable.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Read: 10, Grep: 3, Glob: 4, Bash: 2, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — dev-story (2026-04-04T01:17)\n\n- Branch coverage gap (91.17%): defensive catch blocks hard to trigger in isolation.\n- Test output parsing simplistic — regex for vitest/jest only, falls back for other runners.\n- promisify mock coupling: tests depend on module's use of `promisify(exec)`.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 7, Bash: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest coverage (~30 lines), vitest test (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — code-review (2026-04-04T01:22)\n\n- HIGH: Shell injection via testCommand parameter — fixed with regex validation.\n- HIGH: Shell injection via malicious branch names — fixed with regex validation.\n- MEDIUM: TOCTOU race on branch existence — fixed with re-verification inside mutex.\n- MEDIUM: Missing `// IGNORE:` comment on catch block — fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): No mutex acquisition timeout — starvation risk.\n- LOW (unfixed): No logging in merge path.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput only reads stdout, not stderr.\n- Architecture: testCommand as raw shell string; safer would be execFile with array args.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:coverage (~60 lines x2)\n- Files read: 4 unique, 6 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 4x)\n- Redundant operations: test:coverage ran twice (once pre-fix, once post-fix)\n\n### 18-1-merge-serialization-execution — verification (2026-04-04T01:27)\n\n- BATS test failures (253 `not ok`): pre-existing, not related to story 18-1.\n- AC 7 (runtime-provable) timing NFR4 can't be fully verified with mocked git ops — durationMs mechanism confirmed but 30-second bound untested.\n- npm test ran 4 times in verification subagent (wasteful).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 3, Grep: 1, Write: 1, other: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test (~40 lines), vitest verbose (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: npm test ran 4 times to extract different parts\n\n### 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution — create-story (2026-04-04T01:40)\n\n- No project-context.md found — context gathered from architecture and previous story.\n- onConflict callback design chosen to keep worktree-manager decoupled from merge agent.\n- Risk: Agent may not commit after resolving conflicts — detection logic left to implementation.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff --stat (~8 lines), git log --oneline (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 13 total reads (worktree-manager.ts read 3x at different offsets)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution — dev-story (2026-04-04T01:50)\n\n- onConflict callback passes `driver: undefined as never` — WorktreeManager doesn't hold a driver reference. Caller must override.\n- mainDescription/branchDescription passed as empty strings — WorktreeManager lacks epic descriptions. Caller wires in Epic 19.\n- Pre-existing TypeScript errors in other files (run.test.ts, issue.ts, workflow-engine.test.ts) — not introduced by this story.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 8, Write: 2, Bash: 7, Grep: 3\n- Largest Bash outputs: tsc --noEmit (~50 lines), vitest --coverage (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 2x)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution — code-review (2026-04-04T01:55)\n\n- HIGH: resolveConflicts false positive — unparseable test output (0 passed, 0 failed) treated as success. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: driver: undefined as never would crash at runtime. Fixed via MergeConflictInfo type.\n- MEDIUM: Missing // IGNORE: comments on catch blocks. Fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput duplicated between merge-agent.ts and worktree-manager.ts.\n- LOW (unfixed): buildEscalationMessage is private, only tested indirectly.\n- No integration test for full mergeWorktree + onConflict + resolveConflicts pipeline.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Skill: 1, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:coverage (~80 lines), vitest run (~40-50 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04 (session 2)\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — create-story (2026-04-04T02:10)\n\n- workflow.yaml referenced workflow.md but actual file was workflow.yaml — minor discovery step.\n- No _bmad/bmm/config.yaml (was at _bmad/config.yaml) — required extra glob.\n- Risk: runTestSuite output field asymmetry between worktree-manager.ts and merge-agent.ts needs careful handling during extraction.\n- Risk: Telemetry writer dependency may have changed since story 16-3.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git log --oneline -5 (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One extra Glob for config path\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — dev-story (2026-04-04T02:18)\n\n- writeMergeTelemetry had to be exported for merge-agent two-phase pattern (validate then write telemetry on success). Story spec didn't explicitly require this but it's needed.\n- Branch coverage 96.42% — uncovered branch is nullish coalescing fallback on err.stdout (Istanbul instrumentation edge case).\n- worktree-manager.test.ts read 4 times due to token limits.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 26\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 13, Write: 2, Glob: 4\n- Largest Bash outputs: tsc --noEmit (~32 lines), vitest --coverage (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 12 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 4x)\n- Redundant operations: worktree-manager.test.ts chunked reads, one broken edit fix\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — code-review (2026-04-04T02:27)\n\n- HIGH: coverage type mismatch (undefined vs null) across validator, worktree-manager, merge-agent. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing maxBuffer on exec could truncate large test output. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Missing stderr capture loses diagnostic info. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Telemetry object not typed against canonical TelemetryEntry. Fixed.\n- LOW (unfixed): parseTestOutput first-match regex could pick per-suite counts.\n- LOW (unfixed): writeMergeTelemetry duplicates NDJSON write logic from telemetry-writer.ts.\n- No integration test for full merge-then-validate flow with real git repo.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 16, Grep: 6, Glob: 5, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: vitest run verbose (~50 lines), git diff (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 14 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One redundant glob search for workflow file\n\n### 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation — verification (2026-04-04T02:40)\n\n- `codeharness verify` precondition failure: AGENTS.md was stale for `src/lib` — missing `cross-worktree-validator.ts`. Fixed in parent orchestrator.\n- Coverage for `cross-worktree-validator.ts` specifically could not be isolated to an exact percentage from coverage tool output. Story completion notes claim 100% and all 33 tests exercise every code path.\n- Prior session completed create/dev/review but crashed before updating sprint-status.yaml from `backlog`. Orchestrator detected the mismatch and advanced status.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:unit (~80 lines), vitest --reporter=verbose (~80 lines), npm run test:coverage (~50 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Two separate coverage commands that didn't yield isolated file percentage\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":171,"oldLines":3,"newStart":171,"newLines":18,"lines":[" - Largest Bash outputs: npm run test:unit (~80 lines), vitest --reporter=verbose (~80 lines), npm run test:coverage (~50 lines)"," - Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads"," - Redundant operations: Two separate coverage commands that didn't yield isolated file percentage","+","+### 19-1-epic-completion-detection — create-story (2026-04-04T02:54)","+","+- Sprint-status.yaml not updated by subagent (per instructions) — orchestrator handled.","+- No config.yaml at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` — found at `_bmad/config.yaml` instead.","+- No project-context.md found — not a blocker, sufficient context from epics/architecture.","+- EpicState.status is `string` not a union type — story handles via local `EpicLifecycleStatus` type.","+- All 10 ACs tagged test-provable — pure functions, no I/O.","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: 16","+- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 10, Glob: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: git diff HEAD~3 --name-only (~35 lines), sprint-state.json (~40 lines), git log (~10 lines)","+- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads","+- Redundant operations: None"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
